# Fix Log Issues — Performance, Caching, Errors & Polling

Addresses 12 issues identified in [log_issues.txt](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/Downloads/CreaSearch-main/CreaSearch-main/plans/log_issues.txt) related to excessive polling, high response latencies, cache inconsistency, upload errors, and admin verification failures.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Caching & Rate Limiting

#### [MODIFY] [rateLimit.ts](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/Downloads/CreaSearch-main/CreaSearch-main/backend/src/middleware/rateLimit.ts)

- Replace shared `sensitiveRateLimit` on verification routes with a new `verificationRateLimit` — **per-platform, 100 req/min**
- Key format: `verify:{platform}:{clientId}` so each platform (youtube, instagram, facebook) has its own independent limit
- Export `verificationRateLimit` as a new function that takes a `platform` string parameter

#### [MODIFY] [cache.ts](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/Downloads/CreaSearch-main/CreaSearch-main/backend/src/middleware/cache.ts)

- Reduce verbose `[Cache] HIT` / `[Cache] MISS` logging to [debug](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/Downloads/CreaSearch-main/CreaSearch-main/backend/src/utils/logger.ts#98-107) level (currently [info](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/Downloads/CreaSearch-main/CreaSearch-main/backend/src/utils/logger.ts#108-117) level floods logs)
- This is the root cause of the "Cache Behaviour Inconsistency" log spam — the cache is working correctly but logging every hit/miss at info level makes it look broken

---

#### [MODIFY] [routes.ts](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/Downloads/CreaSearch-main/CreaSearch-main/backend/src/routes.ts)

**Caching additions** (addresses issues: High Latency on Cached Responses, Profile Fetch Latency, Admin Pending Performance, Featured Profiles Latency, Notification Count Spikes):
- Add [cacheMiddleware(30)](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/Downloads/CreaSearch-main/CreaSearch-main/backend/src/middleware/cache.ts#12-66) to `/api/notifications/unread-count` (user-scoped, short TTL)
- Add [cacheMiddleware(30)](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/Downloads/CreaSearch-main/CreaSearch-main/backend/src/middleware/cache.ts#12-66) to `/api/admin/pending`
- Add [cacheMiddleware(120)](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/Downloads/CreaSearch-main/CreaSearch-main/backend/src/middleware/cache.ts#12-66) to `/api/featured-profiles` (public, changes rarely)
- Add [cacheMiddleware(30)](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/Downloads/CreaSearch-main/CreaSearch-main/backend/src/middleware/cache.ts#12-66) to `/api/profiles/:id` (profile detail page)
- Increase TTL on `/api/categories` and `/api/profiles` from `60` to `300` seconds

**Cache invalidation**:
- Call [invalidateCache('/api/profiles')](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/Downloads/CreaSearch-main/CreaSearch-main/backend/src/middleware/cache.ts#67-81) after profile create, update, delete
- Call [invalidateCache('/api/admin/pending')](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/Downloads/CreaSearch-main/CreaSearch-main/backend/src/middleware/cache.ts#67-81) after approve/reject/delete
- Call [invalidateCache('/api/featured-profiles')](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/Downloads/CreaSearch-main/CreaSearch-main/backend/src/middleware/cache.ts#67-81) after feature/unfeature
- Call [invalidateCache('/api/notifications')](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/Downloads/CreaSearch-main/CreaSearch-main/backend/src/middleware/cache.ts#67-81) after creating notification or marking read

**Upload fix** (addresses: Upload Photo Endpoint Runtime Error):
- Change `const { fromBuffer } = await import("file-type")` to use default import pattern:
  ```typescript
  const fileType = await import("file-type");
  const result = await (fileType.fromBuffer || fileType.default?.fromBuffer)(file.buffer);
  ```
- Applies to both photo and video upload handlers (lines 425-426, 457-458)

**Admin verification error handling** (addresses: Manual Admin Verification External API Failures):
- In `/api/admin/verify-instagram-now/:id` and `/api/admin/verify-facebook-now/:id`, when Apify returns 400, propagate the error status to the response instead of silently returning 200
- Add a `warning` field to the response when external verification fails

**Profile creation performance** (addresses: Profile Creation Endpoint Slow Response):
- Move `scoringService.updateProfileScore()` to fire-and-forget (use `.catch()` pattern like email)
- Already done for email; just need to do the same for scoring

