## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification

> [!NOTE]
> No existing test files were found in this project. All verification will be manual.

**Steps:**

1. **Start the backend dev server**: `cd backend && npm run dev`
2. **Upload photo test**: Upload a photo through the UI and confirm no `500` error / `TypeError: fromBuffer is not a function` in server logs
3. **Notification polling test**: Open browser DevTools → Network tab, filter by `unread-count`, and verify calls are ~60s apart (not 30s). Switch to another tab for 2+ minutes and verify no calls are made while hidden
4. **Cache test**: Open DevTools → Network, load the homepage. Check server logs and verify `[Cache] HIT`/`[Cache] MISS` messages are at debug level (not info). Verify `/api/featured-profiles` and `/api/categories` responses are fast after first load
5. **Profile deletion test**: Delete a profile via admin panel. Verify server logs do NOT show repeated `404` responses for `/api/profiles/me` after deletion
6. **Admin verification test**: Trigger admin Instagram/Facebook verification. If Apify returns 400, verify the API response includes an error/warning field (not just success: true)
7. **Profile creation test**: Create a new profile and verify response time is under 1500ms (previously ~2500ms)

> [!TIP]
> Since this is a production app with no automated tests, I recommend you manually test the upload and admin verification paths after deployment. The caching and polling changes can be verified by watching server logs and browser DevTools.
